description: Five new cases are confirmed in the country where 60 staff at a hospital are told to self-isolate.
title: Coronavirus: Health worker among latest Ireland cases
title_page: Coronavirus: Health worker among latest Ireland cases - BBC News
maintext: The Republic of Ireland's chief medical officer Dr Tony Holohan said the risk of contracting coronavirus "in the community is very low" but he added it was inevitable there would be more cases.
